5.2 Structural Issues
1. No __init__.py in tests/ -- pytest can still discover tests without it, but it is non-standard.
2. No conftest.py -- no shared fixtures, no pytest configuration hooks.
3. No pytest configuration -- no marker definitions, no asyncio_mode setting, no test path configuration.
4. No CI/CD configuration -- no GitHub Actions, no test runner script, no Makefile target.
5. Some tests use hardcoded absolute paths (e.g., "D:/Hank" in test_citation_guard.py, test_pruning_rules.py, test_context_hardening.py) which introduces non-portability.
6. Several tests require live dependencies -- test_gemini_context_cache.py needs a live GEMINI_API_KEY; test_agnostic_gateway.py and stability_check_phase_11_18_1.py expect a running gateway at localhost:32553; test_failure_memory_integration.py calls the real get_dynamic_context() without mocks.
