Important Note
The original SQL query you provided referenced a modules table with columns name, module_type, line_count, and edge_count. However, the actual schema in spatial.db uses spatial_modules (columns: module_name, file_path, line_count, num_functions) and spatial_edges (columns: source_module, target_module, relationship, depth). There is no module_type column -- module categorization can be inferred from the module name prefix (e.g., src.clotho.*, cognition.*, tests.*, scripts.*). Edge counts were computed via LEFT JOIN ... GROUP BY source_module on spatial_edges. The database was not modified.
